\begin_layout Section
General hypothesis and dissertation objectives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As the author presented in this chapter, important advances have been done
 in the field of digital analysis of mammograms.
 However there are still large areas of opportunity to improve existing
 systems and to study novel associations of radiologic phenotypes and breast
 cancer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The principal hypothesis that will be validated in this work is: Image informati
on gathered during screening mammography is sufficient to identify image
 sets with radiological findings positively associated with breast cancer.
\end_layout

