\begin_layout Itemize
Demonstrate that characterization of breast parenchyma can be used for the
 development of breast cancer biomarkers using screening mammograms.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
This contribution is measurable with the construction of image-based biomarkers
 for clinical endpoints of breast cancer, and demonstrating their effectiveness
 to distinguish between classes of interest (Cancer vs Normal, Low vs High
 BIRADS score, tumor subtypes)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Determine a set of image analysis methods useful for complete breast characteriz
ation.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
Will be measured by the selection, implementation and evaluation of image
 processing and feature extraction methods that are useful for the construction
 of image-based biomarkers for breast cancer.
 Particularly, the advantages of using a set of features obtained from the
 Minkowski Functionals curves will be analyzed and discussed.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
